SysCalc 
*******
By: The MadGraph team
*******

SysCalc is a package that calculates event weights due to systematical uncertainties.
It requires as input file a systematics file (as generated by MadGraph 5 v. 1.6.0 or 
later plus the Pythia-PGS package v. 2.2.0 or later), and outputs an XML file with 
the uncertainties. It also requires a configuration file specifying the parameters 
to be varied. 
SysCalc uses TinyXML2 for XML parsing, see https://github.com/leethomason/tinyxml2.

Usage: sys_calc sysfile configfile outfile

Note that compilation and running requires LHAPDF to be installed on the system.

The configuration file should look as follows (example):

# Central scale factors
scalefact: 
0.5 1 2
# \alpha_s emission scale factors
alpsfact:
0.5 1 2
# matching scales
matchscale:
32 50 80
# PDF sets and number of members (optional)
PDF:
CT10.LHgrid 53
MSTW2008nlo68cl.LHgrid

The output file has the following format (example for the config file above):
Header:
<header>
  <initrwgt>
    <scale type="central" nentries="3">0.5 1 2</scale>
    <scale type="emission" nentries="3">0.5 1 2</scale>
    <qmatch nentries="3">32 50 80</qmatch>
    <pdf type="CT10.LHgrid" nentries="53"></pdf>
    <pdf type="MSTW2008nlo68cl.LHgrid" nentries="41"></pdf>
  </initrwgt>
</header>

Each event:
<rwgt event="1">
  <scale type="central">1.29393 1 0.786164</scale>
  <scale type="emission">1 1 1</scale>
  <qmatch>1 1 1</qmatch>
  <pdf type="CT10.LHgrid">1.05725 1.05874 1.05587 1.06142 1.053 1.06952 1.04625 1.08195 1.0332 1.06137 1.05186 1.05797 1.05684 1.04904 1.07262 1.05281 1.06127 1.0387 1.06799 1.0515 1.05989 1.06391 1.05405 1.0898 1.02866 1.05604 1.05978 1.06144 1.0542 1.0555 1.05864 1.05826 1.05718 1.07015 1.04585 1.05196 1.07196 1.0568 1.05727 1.0443 1.07429 1.05978 1.05401 1.05889 1.05534 1.05021 1.06662 1.07206 1.04068 1.058 1.05365 1.06536 1.06127</pdf>
  <pdf type="MSTW2008nlo68cl.LHgrid">1.08129 1.08524 1.078 1.0824 1.08002 1.08202 1.08016 1.08211 1.0807 1.07989 1.08323 1.07325 1.08623 1.08335 1.07844 1.0787 1.0822 1.08252 1.07855 1.07962 1.08271 1.08545 1.07401 1.07979 1.08225 1.08026 1.08172 1.07927 1.08312 1.07342 1.09443 1.08084 1.08145 1.08302 1.08023 1.08006 1.08188 1.09386 1.06217 1.08012 1.08155</pdf>
</rwgt>

Johan Alwall, 2012
